programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker is taking a stroll around the Marsh when all of a sudden a giant “owl” falls from the sky. Fearing that the scary bird would devour him, Joe hides himself behind a big rock. Bartle Bee passes by and finds something wrong about this furious “owl”. After a close examination, he discovers that this is not a bird but a paper kite. To fly the kite, Joe slides down a slope to help the kite gain altitude. The kite soars into the sky, taking Joe along on an exciting flight. At first, the fact that he’s ten feet off the ground frightens Joe Croaker. But as he manages to keep the kite under control, he finds himself fascinated by the midair adventure. Joe flies his “glider” and snatches the cheese from Cosmo, which makes the latter really angry. Joe gets completely carried away, when the kite flies into a desert scattered with cacti and becomes out of hand. In the end, Joe crashes in a huge cactus with his “glider”.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker is casting about desperately for something to fill his empty stomach. Luckily for him, he finds some biscuits in a large can. So he jumps right into the can and gobbles up all the biscuits. But after the feast, the frog finds himself unable to get out of the can with an overstuffed belly. He tries all sorts of avenues and finally manages to hop up to the top. Suddenly, the can starts to roll down a slope. Joe freaks out inside the running can and cries for help, which is heard by Cosmo and Bartle Bee who happen to play nearby. They attempt to put a stop to the crazy can, but to no avail. At last, the can is halted on the edge of a cliff. Just when the Bartle Bee and his friends think they are safe, a rock comes running down, knocking the can down into the river. Fortunately enough, the three of them are saved by a large lotus leaf.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Bartle Bee finds a flowering plant in the forest. It is so good-looking that when Bartle Bee leaves, Joe Croaker brings it home and plants it in his back yard. The frog loves the plant and does not allow anyone except himself to touch it. But Cosmo still gets a nimble off one flower petal and the fly becomes extremely aggressive. Cosmo beats Joe Croaker up and makes the frog do his chores and give him massage.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Cosmo finds a discarded solar-powered toy car in the bush. He decides to keep it as a desirable toy. He shows off his new acquisition to Joe Croaker, who is immediately taken with the car as well. Joe Croaker seizes the car from Cosmo and tries to tug it home. As noon comes, the solar-powered car harnesses enough energy from the sun and starts to run on its own. Joe Croaker ties the car to a little tree, trying to keep it still. But fully charged with solar energy, the car breaks free of the restraint and takes Joe Croaker on an exciting road trip. Though a bit scared, Joe gets off on this wild car adventure. He snatches Cosmo’s cheese on the way. The car runs wild again and plunges into a pond, drowning Joe Croaker as well. Cosmo catches up, only to find his cheese cake gone under water.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Cosmo spots a paper boat on the stream. He picks two fine leaves as paddles and begins to go around in his boat. Flutterby is interested in the boat and she asks if she can join Cosmo. Cosmo refuses and Flutterby decides to make one boat on her own. She selects a large leaf and bends it into a boat.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: Briar and Tiki chases their kite to Old Billy’s vegetable patch, and accidentally trample the vegetables. Although they try to correct the deed, but it just get worse. They try to avoid Old Billy in school and hesitate to apologize to him, for fear Old Billy will be angry. Briar tries to get Tiki and apologize to Old Billy. The old man tells them he’s going to the vegetable field to grow new vegetables. Briar and Tiki help him out. At last, they tell Old Billy the truth. The old man doesn’t get angry. Instead, he thinks they are responsible kids.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: Luna-Loo doesn’t want to keep her old or broken toys, and asks her parents to buy her new ones. So she secretly throws away her old toys. When she visits Violet’s home, however, she finds out her friends treasure her toys very much, and remembers the good times she has spent with her toys. Then it rains. Luna-Loo quickly goes outside to find her toys with Violet but can’t find them. She’s feels regret. The next morning, she’s surprised to find out that all her toys are back. It turns out her mom picks up those toys, cleans and mends them. Luna-Loo realizes her mistake and thanks her mom. Violet and Vick come to Luna-Loo’s home and help her modify some old toys. Everyone is happy.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: Summoning the Sun & The Frog Friends
programme.desc: Luna-Loo stays at Violet’s home for the night. They borrow a toy car from Vick powered by solar energy. However, the car runs out of power at night. They are disappointed to find out the sun has already set. They decide to summon the sun. First they to use some “magic spells”, then an ice cream to “entice” the sun to come out. They even mimic the sound of roosters to try to call for the sun. The sun never comes out. Instead, Violet’s parents are woken by the noise. Through a little experiment, they explain to the kids about solar rotation and the switch of night and day.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: Briar and Bramble discover that Old Billy’s office smells bad. They decide to help him get rid of the awful smell. They try to collect some fresh clean air from a flower field with bottles, and bring the air to the office. However, it’s hard to tell whether the fragrance is really inside the bottles. So they decide to use balloons to collect the scent. However, a little hedgehog accidentally pops the balloons when he tries to help them. Old Billy sees them and tells them that the stinky smell will go away if they keep good ventilation in the office.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker is frightened upon spying what he believes to be a monster strolling around the pond. He soon realizes that the “monster” is actually a duck, but can’t work out that it’s in fact a toy duck. Assuming that this Rubber Ducky of Death is scheming to occupy his place, Joe Croaker flips out and decides to teach it a good lesson. He bullies the Rubber Ducky of Death until Bartle Bee sweeps it away. Bartle Bee is determined to rescue what he too, sadly, sees as a real—if unresponsive—duck. Joe gives chase to the two runaways, and they tangle with each other. During the confrontation, Bartle Bee accidentally gives the air-filled toy duck a prick with his sting, causing it to deflate and fly away. Still in the dark, Bartle Bee blames the disappearance of the poor little “creature” on Joe Croaker.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker finds a balloon dinosaur among the grass. The frog has no idea what he has discovered and he really panics at this “dinosaur” that is many times his own size. Joe Croaker begins to attack the balloon with pebbles he picks up from the ground. One of the pebbles bounces off the balloon and hits Bartle Bee’s honey jar on the ground. Though Joe Croaker tells Bartle Bee that he has nothing to do with the broken honey jar, the bee is smart enough to figure it out by himself.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Cosmo eats up all the food Joe Croaker has obtained, which puts the latter into a violate passion. And his mockery about Joe Croaker’s inability to fly adds fuel to fire. The hot-air balloons floating in the sky inspire the frog, who then manages to put together one with all the parts he collects from the garbage can. Flying with the ill-made balloon, Joe Croaker grabs the food from Cosmo and endeavors to catch the fly. But the balloon is too slow for Cosmo, so Joe plays dead to bamboozle Cosmo, who falls for it and ends up being caught. Just at that moment, the candle in the balloon exhausts itself. Both Joe Croaker and Cosmo fall to the ground, where the frog resumes his chase after his little foe.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker comes across a roly-poly toy when he is trying to get some candy near a dumpster. It’s a big smiling face doll. But the frog has no knowledge of what he is facing. He sees the roly-poly as a potential threat to him and the Marsh. Joe Croaker challenges the toy and attempts to take it down. The frog fails and finally he uses a rope to tie the roly-poly toy up.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: As the dung balls keep piling up, McBroom finds himself short of energy to get his work done all by himself. At Bartle Bee’s suggestion, he puts up a recruitment ad to look for someone to help him. The handsome benefits offered on this job allure many insects over, including Hercules Beetle, Snout Beetle and Bartle Bee. To select the best out of the three candidates, McBroom put them on a series of tests where Hercules Beetle stands out to win the position as McBroom’s assistant. Much to McBroom’s disappointment, however, his employee turns out to be quite lazy. So he has to give Hercules Beetle the sack and send him home.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: Hammer the ox is an excellent blacksmith in his village but he only makes weapons. The village head persuades him to sell them at Carrotown because the market there is much larger. Hammer follows his advice and heads for Carrotown. Along the road, the ox tries to promote his weapons to an lumberjack and a watermelon farmer but they all mistake him for a robber and are scared to death.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: Velvet Touch and Trapper are walking through the forest. Unexpectedly, two hedgehogs stand in their way and plan to plunder their valuables. Velvet Touch throws two darts to them, which annoys the two robbers. They contract their bodies into two spiky balls and roll toward her. To protect Velvet Touch, Trapper rushes over and hits them with a long stick. He puts on an awesome Kung Fu show and transforms into Mad Wolf. After Trapper realizes he has spilt the beans, he deliberately loses out to hedgehogs and surrenders to them.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: At night, three animals make a campfire and sit down for a rest. Velvet Touch keeps commending Hammer upon his braveness and complains about Trapper’s cowardice. Velvet Touch thinks Hammer can serve as a good bodyguard and persuades him to go with them together the next day. Hammer accepts her invitation with alacrity. The next morning, they continue on their way. The rabbit suggests to perform juggling acts to attract villagers over and sell Hammer’s weapons to them. Others nod their appreciation.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: Artisan, the richest rooster in the world, writes a piece of calligraphy. All the officials curry favor with Artisan and praise him for creating such a masterpiece. However, the truth is that Artisan is an illiterate and the so-called calligraphy is just his scrawled handwritings. Artisan strolls to the backyard of his palace and sees a kite flying in the sky. On a whim, he decides to make a peerless kite by himself. He orders his attendant to choose the most expensive materials.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: Tiki’s Dancing Lesson & Mom and Me
programme.desc: Tiki admires Violet’s dancing. The kids all want Violet to teach them how to dance. Tiki goes to Violet’s home the next day. On his way there his friends tell him dancing is very difficult. He tries to learn some moves from Vick but he feel discouraged. He still continues to learn as Violet keeps encouraging him. But due to his nervousness, he steps on Luna-Loo many times while practicing. Luna-Loo tries to help him relax but none of the method works. Tiki dances in his own way and relaxes. He finally learns how to dance. He realizes he can’t just give up when others say it’s difficult.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: The Pink Racket & A Promising Flower
programme.desc: The cubs are playing badminton in the kindergarten. Herbert likes the pink racket. However, he overhears the others say the color pink is only for girls. So he does not dare to take the pink one, even though the one he uses is broken during the match. Then Old Billy joins them. The kids laugh at his floral shirt, but Old Billy doesn’t seem to care. Herbert understands he doesn’t need to pay too much attention to others’ opinions, and decides to use the pink racket.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: The cubs are rehearsing a show. At first, Babu acts well in his role. However, he becomes nervous when Warren and Luna-Loo come to watch the rehearsal. He forgets his lines, and can’t act. Babu thinks he didn’t practice enough but Luna-Loo thinks he has stage fright. He gives his role to Ernie Jo. Then Babu’s dad helps him to overcome his stage fright, and asks him to imagine the audience as fruits. At last, Babu doesn’t feel nervous anymore and acts well in the show.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: A Party at Violet’s & Got a Spare?
programme.desc: Violet invites her friends to her home, and has made proper arrangement. She thinks things will go smoothly. However, when her friends come to her house, they don’t want to follow her arrangements. They want to eat cakes and play with the ball. Violet doesn’t know what to do. Her father tells her that she should discuss with her friends about what to do. Violet listens to her friends’ opinions, and they all have fun.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Briar has a toothache and Vick tells him there are bugs eating his teeth, making him anxious. To get the bugs out, they try many methods, such as gargling water, asking Hoo Hoo to peck the bugs out, and singing to lure the bugs out, all of which are proven to be useless. At last, they go to see Nurse Beakman, then they find out the cause of tooth decay, and learn how to protect their teeth.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Violet has a treasure chest, inside which Luna-Loo likes the moon stone the most. That day, Luna-Loo hides the treasure chest somewhere else without Violet’s permission, but what she doesn’t know is that Ms. Lady Jane witnesses the whole thing. The cubs are busy helping Violet look for the chest, while Luna-Loo is invited to Ms. Lady Jane’s office, where she hears Violet’s words about how she cherishes the chest. Luna-Loo realizes what she has done is not right. Ms. Lady Jane comes in. She asks Luna-Loo to return a screwdriver to Vick, and tells her that even though she likes the screwdriver, she can’t keep it because she’s not the owner. Luna-Loo puts the chest back and makes a confession to her friends.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.sub-title: The Family Visit & You Get What You Put In
programme.desc: Little Briar misbehaves at kindergarten and refuses to apologize to the other kids. Ms. Olivia happens to go to the kids’ home for family visits. Briar is afraid that mom will learn about his behavior at kindergarten, so he tries various means to stop the family visit. Despite of this, Ms. Olivia still meets Briar’s mom. Seeing he could do nothing to stop the family visit, Briar tells the truth. Ms. Olivia tells Briar that he needs to confront his problems, and Briar learns a valuable lesson.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.sub-title: Tiki the Weatherman & Herby’s Helpful Apples
programme.desc: Old Billy forecasts the weather right, and Tiki asks Old Billy to teach him how to forecast a rainy day. Tiki makes notes and memorizes it. The other kids at Pine Tree Kindergarten plan to have a picnic, and Tiki tells them the weather will be sunny. However, just when the kids are going to have the picnic, it rains. Tiki goes to find Old Billy and asks him what’s wrong with the weather forecast. Old Billy explains that nature changes constantly and that only by studying hard could they make weather forecasts as accurate as possible.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.sub-title: Kitty the Tiger & The Magic Words
programme.desc: An uninvited guest, Kitty the tiger, sneaks into the drawing class, and shocks the whole class. But later this adorable tiger wins everybody’s heart. They like her, and volunteer to look after her. Kitty makes much trouble. However to make her happy, Prince Tiki lets her have his favorite bag. During naptime, kitty misses her mom so much that she can’t stop crying. Then the kids sing for her to help her sleep. It’s time to say goodbye. Everybody feels sad to part with her. Ms. Olivia promises that Kitty will attend the kindergarten when she grows up, making them happy again.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker picks up a bouncy ball among the grass and takes it home. This small ball bounces around in a way that the frog cannot control. Joe Croaker now is standing on it and the bouncy ball begins to roll down a slope. The frog attempts tries to stop the ball but he simply is not able to mange. It takes the frog some agility and luck to avoid the rocks and tree branches in his way and finally he is stopped by one of McBroom’s dung balls.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Bartle Bee accidentally sets foot in a place studded with numerous full-blown flowers. Overjoyed, he plans to have a good time collecting nectar there. Then there comes a mean bee who tries to beat him up, accusing Bartle of trespassing on his turf. Intimidated, Bartle has to run away from that flourishing land. Flutterby learns of the whole story and decides to help her little buddy punish the bad bee. She paints two horrible huge eyes on the leaves and uses them to scare off the villainous bee. Then Bartle Bee sets up the leaves in the field, but a gust of wind blows them off to the ground, revealing the truth to the vicious bee. In his pursuit of Bartle Bee, the bully bee runs into a big bird which he believes to be a fake one for setting him up. He throws stones at the bird, only to be chased by the furious creature. Just when the bird is about to swallow him, Bartle Bee and Flutterby show up. They distract the bird and save the bee’s life. In the end, the three of them put behind the grudge and become friends.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker comes across a slingshot in the Marsh. He soon realizes that it is a decent swing. The frog then takes a thorough examination of the slingshot. He is convinced that he can shoot some pebbles with this new toy he just found. The pebbles cause damage to the neighboring insects and Joe Croaker could not stop there. He finds a box of pushpins and starts to shoot them.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Cosmo brags about seeing a long train in front of Joe Croaker. The fly can see the world from above in the mid air but Joe Croaker cannot. This upsets the frog. Joe Croaker figures that if he climbs up to the top of the tree, he will be able to get a better view there. But sadly for Joe Croaker, on a long list of the things he can achieve, climbing isn’t one of them. Advised by Cosmo, Joe Croaker makes many failed attempts to climb up the tree. First he tries to do it by sticking the double-sided tape to his limbs, which results in a heavy fall from the tree. Then Cosmo fetches him a rope with a big hook that is intended to be attached to the tree and help Joe up. But it falls and almost has Cosmo crushed. In the end, on Bartle’s suggestion, Cosmo helps Joe Croaker build up a firm ladder which Joe Croaker takes to reach the top of the tree. But when up there, Joe realizes that he is afraid of heights!

Old Billy explains that nature changes constantly and that only by studying hard could they make weather forecasts as accurate as possible.

programme.desc: The Cheetah is back from paint! It’s not an illusion… you don’t need to adjust your television set the fastest cat on the planet is back! Stacey is going to tell you all about what it took to get this beautiful beast back in the Gearz garage. In case you get lost in the magnificent Blue Moon candy paint, Stacey will be able to find you with our Gladiator search and rescue build, as he ties the project in with S.A.R.D.U.S.—Search and Rescue Dogs of the United States. This episode is going to keep you howling at the moon!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: There is no better way to wrap up this season of Gearz than to put a wrap on our Search and Rescue Gladiator build. Over 13 episodes, 13 modifications were made to this Jeep to turn it into something ANY outdoors person would love, and Stacey takes us through the build one last time before we let this Gladiator leave the garage. But with every project that leaves, a new one finds its way in and a ‘73 Ford F250 holds plenty of promise as Stacey introduces the newest build… Blue Steel!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Stacey digs into the mysteries of finding a good project vehicle. Because it’s not just about tools and techniques, sometimes you have to be part detective to read the clues that tell you about the history of the vehicle. After that, he walks through budget and how to decide what level of project you need to do. It’s like a car whispering master class from one of the best in the business, and you’re only gonna see it on Gearz!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Sometimes the biggest problems you face on a project are fixing someone else’s fixes! You know what I’m talking about. The modified vehicle you buy, only to find that the modifications weren’t done too well! Stacey takes on old ‘77 Jeep CJ5 and starts correcting some issues by dumping the old sagging suspension and replacing it with a new 4” lift and some new wheels and tires. If you’ve got an old vehicle that has been hacked on, there are some easy fixes to get it back on the road safely.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: There is nothing more comfortable than an old pair of Levi’s, unless it’s an old Jeep. Stacey shows how easy it is to update a classic, without losing the classic feel of the vehicle. The exhaust system, steering and brakes are all areas that our ‘77 Levi edition Jeep could benefit from, so Stacey takes it under the knife and shows that the only thing better than an old, faded pair of Levi’s jeans... is a faded Levi Edition CJ5 with the right upgrades to it. Far out man!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Stacey takes a trip to the ‘Days Gone By’ Museum located just outside of Nashville. This place is awesome! From horse drawn carriages, to a DC3, to an enormous collection of tractors… so much of America’s manufacturing history is under one roof. It’s a wild ride through decades of mechanical achievements and a lesson to the younger generation of gearheads as to what the American spirit is capable of! There’s also a working garage where the owner specializes in building hot rods and the restoration of the vehicles you find in the museum. Speaking of restoration work, Stacey shares some tips on wiring that will help keep you sane when it comes time to rewire your project vehicle. Lots of history and plenty of practical advice on Gearz!

programme.desc: Porsche collector, customizer, and Urban Outlaw, Magnus Walker is a world-wide rock star to fans of the German car company. So, when Caffeine & Octane producers invited him to travel cross country to tell the story of a hidden Porsche collection tangled in a North Georgia Vineyard, they were surprised when he signed on. No sour grapes here, what Walker found at the Wolf Mountain Winery will impress even those with the most refined palette for Porsches.

programme.title: Caffeine & Octane
programme.desc: Demetrio Montalvo likes American music, American food, and especially American cars. Only one problem - Demetrio lives in Cuba. A Visa, bestowed to him from some American friends in high places, lets him travel to the States to search for tough to find automotive parts and attend his favorite car show. Showing up to Caffeine & Octane in a cool caddy is the easy part. Picking parts to take back home presents a unique set of challenges for the Cuban car builder; Formula Drift racer Federico Sceriffo brings the first ever Formula Drift Ferrari to C&O.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Today’s muscle cars are something else, from Hellcat engines to Boss 9’s, and the ever popular LS swap, there’s a lot of muscle under the hoods of custom and production vehicles. But these cars didn’t just show up with all that horsepower, no, there’s a long lineage of American muscle cars, and Stacey takes you on a tour of a new an old muscle. There’s something to be said about the drive of the American auto industry and how our country built the muscle car legacy.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Chances are, if you’ve pulled a car or truck out of a barn or a field or got a “steal” of a deal on craigslist, there’s going to be some metal work in your near future. Well, Stacey’s no different from the rest of us, and just to prove that he’s got a classic Jeep FC150 that needs some TLC in the metal department. Hang out with us as Stacey talks repair or new fabrication when facing dents, warps, and rust… and check out the nasty corner dent on the FC as Stacey explains how to read a dent and the many different techniques you can use to “Bump” some metal and pull that dent out. You won’t need a box full of tools either, a couple of different hammers and some on and off dolly work will have the sheet metal back in shape quicker than you thought.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Ever wonder what goes into making a supercar a supercar? Top speed? Names like Ferrari or Lamborghini? The price? The pedigree? It can be really confusing, and nobody can agree… but Stacey takes you on a tour of several supercars and tries to figure out what exactly does make a supercar a supercar? From Rolls, to Lambo, to Viper, to GT and even a vintage Pantera, we’ve got your supercar fix on GearZ.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Stacey dives deep into the exciting and unpredictable world of the automotive auctions, as we follow two potential sellers to Mecum. If you’ve ever thought about selling or buying a classic car or pickup truck at auction, you need to see this show! Can it be full of frenetic bidding and sky-high prices? Sure… but we show how to approach an auction as an enthusiast or a collector and the kind of mindset you need to play the auction game! From original Hemi Cuda’s, to Iconic racing vehicles, to average daily drivers, we run across them all and give you a front row seat to the hottest game in the automotive world today. Let the gavel fall!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Old Faded Levi is back in the shop on Gearz, as Stacey deals with the final upgrade that every old CJ jeep can benefit from… A GOOD TOP! Notorious for leaky seals and bad latches, original jeep soft tops are probably the reason there are so many rusty jeeps around today! Fortunately, Stacey has a solution with a new Bestop Supertop. After that we go thru a few misconceptions a person may have when they go to replace weatherstripping on their project. It’s all about keeping out the wind and water.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Quick, what’s a tribologist....or lubricity, or stiction? If you’re thinking STAR TREK,… you’re wrong! If you’re thinking oil…. You’re right, and you’re gonna learn all about those things today on How to make your oil live long & prosper After that, Stacey digs into the delicate topic of missing VIN tags, titles, and paperwork, and walks thru the steps and challenges to getting your project legal so you can drive it down the road. Only on GearZ!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: On this episode, Stacey leaves the garage to visit a local car builder and his son. What he finds is not only one, but two, great projects that bridge the generation gap and the differences between classic hot rod and a road-course tuner build. These two may not agree on everything when it comes to the cars they build and drive, but they can agree that time in the shop with each other is time well spent! Then hang around as Stacey takes us through the steps of getting a 1941 Ford Coupe running and why taking it for a spin right away is not always the best thing to do. Only on GearZ!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Stacey shows how America’s oldest tool company, Cornwell Tools, is changing the way you look at tool storage with their Platinum Series boxes and accessories. Never again will you have to sell a small box to get a larger one. With the Platinum series, you can just add to it to create your own custom tool center. Like Legos, but much cooler! After that, he rolls out one of the biggest and baddest toolboxes around - The Iron Giant! But massive boxes and tool storage won’t do you any good if you can’t utilize it properly, so we also show you how to do that with the unique tool grid system. Then hang around as Stacey shows how to measure and calculate for new wheels and tires on “Old Crusty"—his M715 Jeep truck. If you have an odd vehicle and need custom wheels for it, you need to see this show!

programme.title: Caffeine & Octane
programme.desc: Take apart and assemble a motor in less than 30 minutes? Sure, NASCAR pit crews can make the claim, but can a rag tag group of kids with names like Jelly Donut, Butter Bean, and Wonder Woman claim the pit fame? Host Rickey Gadson heads to the Sims Academy to settle a bet. This ultra fast half-hour edition of Caffeine & Octane also includes a builder’s take on an Ultra Four Unlimited Off-Road Racer; Ryan Hardwick joins the gang at Caffeine and Octane.

programme.title: Caffeine & Octane
programme.desc: On this edition of Caffeine & Octane, we’ll go inside the head of Master Builder Bryan Fuller at the SEMA car show, the largest annual trade show in the country; SEMA always brings out the best in the automotive industry. From a jaw dropping Javelin to a multimillion-dollar Pagani, Brian will prove to you, what happens in Vegas, doesn’t always stay in Vegas! Ryan Hardwick guest hosts and ventures deep into the C&O lots to find his favorite ride of the day.

programme.title: Caffeine & Octane
programme.desc: Caffeine & Octane is back at the beach on Jekyll Island with a focus on cars and families. Fathers & sons, with their barn-find Pilot House trucks and Plymouth Satellites, call cars the glue that keeps them bonded together with C&O being the best place to show them off.

programme.title: Caffeine & Octane
programme.desc: Early spring in Jekyll Island, GA is something to behold. Add a few hundred of the country’s coolest rides for Caffeine & Octane at the Beach, and it’s a thing of beauty. Models that blasted the glass ceiling of expectation at the all makes and models show include a hand-built, twin-turbo Tucker, a one-off 1951 Kaiser Drag’N, and a Roadkill Custom known only as Blasphemi!

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Stacey Preps the bed of the NAPA Perfect additions truck. From rolling out Herculiner to installing transfer tank, truck boxes, and even a combination generator/compressor, this big Ford begins its Perfect Additions transformation. He also throws in a wiring tech that will keep you from getting your wires crossed.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Stacey tackles power gains at the air intake, modifies the computer and replaces the stock exhaust before addressing a 2” front-end suspension lift kit. He moves on to give the truck some extra height and support in the rear of the truck where payload weight can be a serious issue. After the suspension is in place, new wheels and tires bring the truck back down to the ground. Stacey also covers several tools that will help you get that old exhaust out from under your vehicle.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: The SR-71 Rapid Tool Express is really taking off! We get our custom chassis from the Roadster Shop—those guys know a thing or two about quality builds. Engine Master Jon Kaase delivers a one-of-a-kind engine to power our SR-71. This build is coming together fast! With the body back on, Stacey takes you through some of the other mods that are going to tie this build in with the SR-71 Blackbird. Get ready, ya’ll, we’ve got loads of good stuff on GearZ.

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: Season 13 is off and rumbling with Stacey showing off the new exhaust system for the SR-71 Rapid Tool Express project. From the headers to the tailpipes, this exhaust is going to scream! After that, it’s chassis details as Stacey lays out a plan for pedals, brakes and a fuel tank. Of course You can’t have an SR-71 inspired build without some killer wheels and wait ‘til you see what Stacey and our good friends at Neely Precision come up with. It’s all good, and it’s all here, this week on GearZ

programme.title: Stacey David's Gearz
programme.desc: The biggest Toy in the shop is back... HEAVY METAL! Yes... Our old junk yard International Tow Truck rolls back into the garage as the freshly painted cab returns from the Hot Rot Institute. And it’s not just any paint, It’s Razzleberry from Axalta that’s so candy, you’ll want to take a bite! But there’s no time for that because Stacey jumps right in to putting a face and interior back in this old junkyard dog. The result will make you really glad that he rescued this one from the crusher! It’s recycling at it’s best... it’s GEARZ!

programme.title: The Smurfs

Papa Smurf realizes that Born Rotten is from another planet, and he instructs Feathers to return him to his home before Gargamel finds them.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Grouchy learns that emotions can be great, particularly after the villainess of Chlorhydris creates a heart of ice to magically drain every one of care and love.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Jealous of the attention Vanity Smurf receives when he breaks his toe, Jokey Smurf feigns sickness in hopes of getting recognition. Unfortunately, his ploy turns against him and instead of loving care all he receives is the proverbial pound of curse.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: A swamp monster kidnaps Baby as a gift for a witch. The witch, who thinks no one loves her, is amazed when Baby shows affection. When Papa comes to rescue Baby, he makes the witch understand that the loyal swamp monster has always loved her.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Hogatha manages to obtain the magic golden earrings of Sonoria that will enable her to hear Smurfy voices from afar. Following Lazy's snores, she almost reaches the Smurf Village until Harmony's horn-blasts blow in her earrings and she flies home in a rage.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.sub-title: The Smurfs And The Money Tree
programme.desc: The wicked wizard Gargamel has come up with yet another diabolical plan with the help of his mother, who isn't much nicer than him. He wants to tempt the Smurfs with money of which they have no notion. Will Greedy take the bait?

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Papa Smurf recalls Dreamy's exciting voyage on the high seas and his gripping adventures with sea turtles, whales, desert islands... and pirates!

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The Smurfs learn that the mind is more powerful than matter when they are fooled by a quack's outrageously expensive miracle tonic. But Papa Smurf cures the Smurfs of their temporary naivete and the charlatan of his villainy.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: In another Smurf theatrical super-production based – very loosely – on Alexandre Dumas' characters, a masterpiece of the stage is created, with a few lines from Romeo and Juliet thrown in.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: This is spook-a-Smurf eve, and all the Smurfs get ready for the fancy dress party... But Brainy Smurf gets hold of Papa Smurf's Book of Magic, and all the Smurfs are changed into hideous but funny creatures. Yet danger lurks...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: A war is raging in the Middle Ages. Knights in armor in hot pursuit inadvertently destroy the Smurfs Village so a small band of Smurfs decide to avenge this wrongdoing. Won't Papa Smurf think this is too human-like a reaction?

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Periwinkle, a vain Pixie, is upset when her magic mirror tells her that Vanity is the fairest, not she. Periwinkle kidnaps Vanity, but the rest of the Smurfs come to Vanity's rescue. Periwinkle sees the error of her ways and they become friends.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The Smurfs befriend a maiden in distress who is betrothed to Gargamel by convincing her father that the foolish wizard is insane.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Trying a new spell on the Smurfs backfires when Gargamel turns himself into stone. The Smurfs are delirious with joy. Their archenemy will make them suffer no more!

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Get up early in the morning, before any other Smurf is out of bed, to prepare a scrumptious Smurfberry muffin. Spend all morning on preparing Smurf delicacies for lunch. Than all afternoon to have dinner ready – and delicious – on time. And do you get so much as a thank you form the Smurfs? So Greedy Smurf quits. The Village is in trouble... And soon, so is Greedy.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Hogatha disguises herself as the Golden Smurf Award to catch the Smurfs in order to use them as the main ingredient in her beauty cream. Vanity convinces her to try his recipe and before long, the wicked sorceress is covered with mud and sent careening over the hills into Gargamel's house.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Brainy Smurf has decided to dedicate himself to the wellbeing of his fellow Smurfs. He is going to cure them of all ills... With a little help from the evil Gargamel!

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Grouchy, the Smurf who hates everything, doubly hates his own birthday party and goes to hide in Shadow Swamp... He is going to meet strange beings and stranger adventures while the other Smurfs search for him...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Flighty Smurf, as his name implies, can't make his own mind up about anything. The other Smurfs take him to the forest for a survival test in which he can find his way home only by making decisions. He ends up in Balthazar's castle.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Periwinkle, a vain Pixie, is upset when her magic mirror tells her that Vanity is the fairest, not she. Periwinkle kidnaps Vanity, but the rest of the Smurfs come to Vanity's rescue. Periwinkle sees the error of her ways and they become friends.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Harmony unwittingly signs a contract with Ghost Writer for a symphony that imprisons him in a ghostly nightclub for life! Papa Smurf demands a jury trial with ghostly jurors and a judge that finds Harmony innocent and Ghost Writer guilty of plagiarism.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Yes, there can be too much of a good thing. When an accident happens to Papa Smurf's magic formula and he ends up multiplied by two, the Smurfs are elated: two Papa Smurfs can give twice the good counsel and twice the loving that one can. But after a while, things get too complex in the Village. Especially when another accident doubles the number of Gargamels!

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Gargamel has thrown in his slime pond so much poisonous muck that the water becomes enchanted and Gargamel, after falling in, suddenly finds himself much smaller that he would wish. Actually he is going to be so small that Papa Smurf will save him!

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: An evil imp gives Smurfette dancing shoes and then tricks her into promising to marry him. All her little friends rush to her rescue and Papa Smurf magically puts the dancing shoes on the imp. He is forced to dance off into the night.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Fortachon descubre a un caballero que lo ayuda a combatir a un Dragon, pero este huye y deja a Fortachon defendiendo a los Pitufos.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: Goloso Y La Olla De Estofado
programme.desc: El hada buena Guinilda entrega a Pitufo Goloso una olla magica, pero Pitufo Filosofo hace que se desborde e inunde la aldea y el bosque. La bienintencionada hada acude al rescate y pide que le devuelvan la olla para darsela a un orfanato de ninos hambrientos.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Papa Pitufo le da a Pitufo Debilucho una crema especial para que la utilice y recupere su fuerza. Poco despues, recibe una condecoracion por sus heroicos actos de fortaleza, y su autoestima se dispara cuando se da cuenta de que la crema es simplemente mermelada de pitufrutas.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: Armonia La Estrella De La Funcion
programme.desc: Pitufo Armonia firma inconscientemente un contrato con Escritor Fantasma para escribir una sinfonia, lo que hace que quede atrapado en un club nocturno fantasmal para siempre. Papa Pitufo exige un juicio con un jurado y un juez de fantasmas, que declaran inocente a Pitufo Armonia y culpable de plagio a Escritor Fantasma.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos hambrientos descubren una cueva en donde se encuentra oculta comida congelada custodiada por un trol tambien congelado quien fue encarcelado debido a su avaricia por un diamante magico. Mientras los Pitufos descongelan la cueva Gargamel roba la comida, pero el diamante magico lo transforma en una masa helada y el trol liberado ayuda gustosamente a los Pitufos a cargar la comida de regreso a su aldea.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Armonia ya no es bienvenido en el coro de los Pitufos: canta de una manera demasiado desafinada. Sin embargo, Papa Pitufo le entrega un amuleto que le convertira en un virtuoso del canto. Y, por si fuera poco, aqui llega Hogata...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Fortachon descubre lo que es estar incapacitado cuando se rompe la pierna. Pitufo Carpintero crea para el una pitufisilla de ruedas, un invento que le proporcionara algo de movilidad a Pitufo Fortachon. Pero, de repente, el malvado mago Gargamel aparece en escena.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Filosofo esta harto. Los Pitufitos y Sasita siguen inventandose historias sobre el con desagradables consecuencias. Por eso, prepara una formula magica, extraida del libro de hechizos de Papa Pitufo, que hace que los pequenos Pitufos crezcan y crezcan cada vez que dicen mentiras. Pero no habia contado con que ahora Gargamel tiene una forma de capturar a los Pitufitos.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El rey Symphonium envia a su pelicano Satchelmouth para capturar a la orquesta de Pitufo Filosofo y llevar a todos hasta su isla. Pitufo Sonador se pone al timon de un barco y se hace a la mar para rescatarlos. Cuando Pitufo Sonador se marea, Pitufo Filosofo toma el mando y encabeza el equipo de rescate que libera a los Pitufos capturados.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Hay algun tipo de poder maligno en la corona del Titan que Minero encuentra bajo tierra, y Avaricioso acaba sucumbiendo a el. Cuando Gargamel aparece con una de sus fechorias en mente, todo se acaba enrevesandose.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Te despiertas temprano por la manana, antes de que los demas Pitufos se hayan levantado de sus camas, para preparar sabrosos bizcochos de pitufrutas. Dedicas toda la manana a preparar pitufimanjares para el almuerzo. Despues, toda la tarde a tener la deliciosa cena lista a tiempo. ¿Y acaso los demas Pitufos te dan siquiera las gracias? Asi pues, Pitufo Goloso renuncia. La aldea esta en problemas... y pronto, tambien lo esta Pitufo Goloso.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Papa Pitufo se encuentra indefenso cuando se le acaban las bayas magicas que utiliza para sus pociones. Afortunadamente, los pequenos Pitufos encuentran un bebe de dragon en el bosque y con su ayuda...

programme.title: El Pitufo Vanidoso
programme.desc: El espejo magico de Gargamel deja atrapado a Pitufo Vanidoso dentro de el, asi que Pitufina y Pitufo Filosofo se apresuran para rescatarlo. Una vez estan dentro del mundo del espejo, provocan una gran explosion que rompe el cristal del espejo, pudiendo volver sanos y salvos al pueblo.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Grunon aprende que las emociones pueden ser fantasticas, sobre todo despues de que la malvada Clorhidris cree un corazon de hielo para despojar a todos de la bondad y el amor.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Esta vez, Gargamel tiene un plan infalible. Sin hacer caso de la risa burlona de Azrael, el malvado hechicero ha perfeccionado una sustancia magica a la que ha llamado «polvo temerario», que convertira a todos los Pitufos en temerarios e intrepidos aventureros. ¿Caera Papa Pitufo en la trampa de Gargamel? ¿Atrapara su enemigo a todos los Pitufos? ¿Tendra esta historia un final feliz?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Una aventura dramatica y conmovedora... Pitufina y su mascota Re chillido. La pequena Pitufina esta inundada en lagrimas. ¿Podran los demas pitufos consolarla?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Guillermo se encuentra en el castillo de sus amigos Selwyn y Tallulah cuando el tio Fenwick, el amigable fantasma, le pide ayuda para atrapar a algunos parientes que le acechan. Guillermo acude a los Pitufos en busca de ayuda, y asi comienza una divertida persecucion...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El malvado brujo Gargamel pide al mago Balthazar una receta para capturar a los pitufos. Implica secuestrar a la Madre Naturaleza para impedir la llegada de la Primavera. Por suerte, los pitufos salvan la situacion.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cuando el Pitufo Filosofo pierde sus gafas deja caer las cosas, tropieza con los objetos, y se convierte en tan patoso como el Pitufo Tontin, que ahora tiene que leer a Filosofo y ayudarle a manejarse. Esta experiencia hace que Filosofo se sienta culpable por la forma en la que siempre se ha burlado de Tontin. Una vez que recibe un nuevo par de gafas, le trata con mas respeto.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El malvado hechicero Gargamel acude una vez mas a Esmeralda, la adivinadora, la cual se las ingenia para hacerse con el dinero de Gargamel. Cuando es el turno de los Pitufos, les hace creer que existe un arbol de la suerte...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cada manana, los duendecillos del agua depositan rocio sobre las hojas del bosque. No imaginas todo lo que ocurrira cuando Pitufo Miedoso se transforme con la varita magica que crea las gotas de rocio...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: La Cama Voladora De Papa Pitufo
programme.desc: Gargamel lanza un hechizo a la nueva cama de Papa Pitufo para que cualquiera que duerma en ella sea transportado al lugar con el que este sonando. Los ensuenos de los Pitufos les llevan a un barco, un castillo y, por ultimo, hasta Gargamel. Consiguen escapar cuando Pitufo Torpe se queda dormido y suena con su hogar.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Todos sabemos que Pitufo Grunon odia varias cosas. Pero la cosa que odia mas que nada es el agua, cuando hay suficiente para que se pueda ahogar. Pitufo Grunon no sabe nadar. Y cuando los Pitufos notan esto y le tratan de ensenar como sobrevivir en el agua, el malvado mago Gargamel hace que todo sea un poco mas peligroso de lo que deberia ser...

programme.title: No Puedo Pitufar La Musica
programme.desc: No hay nada que la hechicera Clorhidris odie tanto como el amor en el mundo. Le gustaria que el amor desapareciera de la faz de la tierra y, para conseguirlo, ha decidido comenzar por la musica. Lanza un hechizo a un cuerno magico que absorbera la melodia de las canciones... en especial, de las canciones de los Pitufos. Con la ayuda de su amiga Laconia, es posible que los Pitufos consigan echar por tierra el malvado plan de Clorhidris...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: La encantadora Allura posee una esfera magica muy especial cuya energia, segun ella misma dice, puede levantar el animo e inspirar a aquellos faltos de inspiracion. Todo lo que hay que hacer es sostener la esfera con las manos... Es cierto que la esfera fomenta la inspiracion, pero solo hasta cierto punto. Sin embargo, sus efectos secundarios pueden ser muy peligrosos, tal como descubren los Pitufos cuando se hacen adictos a la esfera...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos descubren el espiritu deportivo, la alegria y la amista cuando llevan a cabo sus primeros "Juegos Pitufos". Los Pitufos deciden ponerse en forma tras casi perder contra el gato Azrael.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos descubren una Fuente de la Juventud cuidada por un espantoso Troll que roba el libro magico de Papa Pitufo.

programme.title: La Abominable Bestia De La Nieve
programme.desc: Pitufo Filosofo y sus amigos organizan una jornada en la Montana de Hielo para buscar la rara flor de la nieve para Papa Pitufo. Encuentran una terrorifica bestia de la nieve, pero acaban siendo amigos gracias a la amabilidad de Pitufina, y les ayuda a encontrar la minuscula flor.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Gargamel, el malvado mago, ha ideado un nuevo plan para capturar a los Pitufos: ha construido una estatua gigante con la forma de Papa Pitufo. Espera que, al verla, los Pitufos lleven la estatua a su aldea.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: En un esfuerzo por conseguir que Papa Pitufo tenga algo de tranquilidad, Pitufo Filosofo usa uno de los hechizos de Papa Pitufo para crear una barrera de sonido magica alrededor de la aldea. Papa Pitufo no es capaz de deshacer el hechizo y envia a los Pitufitos, que han quedado atrapados fuera de la aldea, a un hacedor de ruidos. Bebe Pitufo se lleva una botella de ruido de casa del hacedor de ruidos, y asi consiguen romper la barrera.

programme.title: La Carrera De Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Carpintero ha ideado un nuevo invento: el pitufimovil. Todos los Pitufos tienen su propio vehiculo personalizado y todos (o casi todos) disfrutan dando una vuelta en ellos. Sin embargo, el malvado mago Gargamel se aprovecha de la idea y empieza a causar problemas a los Pitufos...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: ¿Que es esa pequena luna que ha llegado del cielo? Es un globo de barro cubierto de crateres y habitado por los Lodosos, una familia de criaturas que vienen del cielo y comen y salpican barro. No todos los Pitufos demuestran entusiasmo por los visitantes...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Gargamel y Baltasar se ponen a los mandos de un Robotin gigante para obligar al rey Gerard a que les entregue a Pitufo Robotin. Cuando el Robotin esta a punto de destruir el castillo, Giganton, el nuevo, enorme y extrano amigo de Pitufo Robotin, vence al Robotin. Pitufo Robotin sufre danos durante la batalla, pero Pitufo Carpintero lo arregla y le implanta una caja de voz que le permite decir «¡Hola!».

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Armonia ya no es bienvenido en el coro de los Pitufos: canta de una manera demasiado desafinada. Sin embargo, Papa Pitufo le entrega un amuleto que le convertira en un virtuoso del canto. Y, por si fuera poco, aqui llega Hogata...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Bromista se pasa de la raya con sus bromas cuando Clorhidris cae victima de una de ellas. Para vengarse de los Pitufos, crea un hechizo para robar su sentido del humor. Pitufo Grunon, que ya de por si no tenia sentido del humor, se hace con la pocion de humor y rompe el hechizo.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Natural y Travieso roban la formula de Gargamel para hacer otro Pitufo - otra pitufa para acompanar a Pitufina. Asi pues, crean a Sassette, que crea problemas por doquier. Haciendo uso de su pocion, Papa Pitufo convierte la malvada creacion de Gargamel en una simpatica Sassette.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Las pinturas del malvado Maestro son capaces de tele portar a sus modelos dentro del cuadro...para siempre! Papa pitufo le dice a Pintor que cambie las pinturas y en poco tiempo Maestro acaba dentro de uno de sus cuadros, al lado de su modelo de ensueno: Pitufina.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Hay algun tipo de poder maligno en la corona del Titan que Minero encuentra bajo tierra, y Avaricioso acaba sucumbiendo a el. Cuando Gargamel aparece con una de sus fechorias en mente, todo se acaba enrevesandose.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos estan tan absortos con el nuevo juguete de Pitufo Carpintero que se olvidan de dar de comer a Puppy. Gargamel atrae a Puppy hacia una jaula con comida y le mantiene cautivo para pedir un rescate: los secretos magicos de los Pitufos. Los Pitufitos distraen a Gargamel con el juguete durante el tiempo necesario para rescatar a Puppy, y prometen no volver a dejarlo desatendido.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Las preocupaciones de Papa Pitufo hacen que le salgan verrugas. La unica forma de librarle de esta enfermedad causada por la indecision es que frote el cuerno de uno de los Verrugosos, los desalinados, viscosos, estupidos y brutales enemigos de las haditas del Bosque de los Sauces...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: Una Choza No Es Un Hogar
programme.desc: Gargamel desea tener una choza mas grande, y recurre al Gran libro de hechizos para conjurar un nuevo hogar. Sin embargo, todos sus hechizos le salen del reves y esto le convence de que no hay ningun sitio como el hogar.

programme.title: El Libro De Bromas De Bromista
programme.desc: Las cajas sorpresa de Pitufo Bromista ya no resultan divertidas para los demas Pitufos. Pitufo Bromista busca nuevas ideas en su «Gran libro de las bromas», pero esas ideas son aun peor recibidas en la aldea. Y entonces, Gargamel llega con algunas bromas de su propia cosecha...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Gargamel inventa la leyenda del Pitufo Hechicero para enganar a Papa Pitufo y sus amigos Pitufos y conducirlos hacia una trampa en lo alto de la montana. Papa Pitufo, con su ingenio, engana al mago con algo de sus propia magia y Gargamel es perseguido montana abajo y devuelto de nuevo a su castillo.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Un terrible gigante ayuda a Gargamel a capturar a los Pitufos para hacer una rica sopa, pero tendra que enfrentar a Papa Pitufo primero.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El malvado hechicero Gargamel acude una vez mas a Esmeralda, la adivinadora, la cual se las ingenia para hacerse con el dinero de Gargamel. Cuando es el turno de los Pitufos, les hace creer que existe un arbol de la suerte...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cuando el hada de las flores aparece en el pueblo de los Pitufos, todos se enamoran de su encanto e inteligencia. Y pronto se daran cuenta de que se convertira en una especie de mama pitufo para todos...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El malvado mago Gargamel ha conseguido capturar a Pitufina. Ahora, se dispone a administrarle un suero de la verdad para descubrir todos los secretos de Papa Pitufo... pero Gargamel comete un gran error y le da a Pitufina una formula de las mentiras.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: La reina Agripina no dejara que su hijo, el principe Godofredo, se case con la dulce Priscila. Ella quiere como nuera a una chica que sea capaz de mostrarle algo que nunca antes haya visto. Cuando Hogata se entera y descubre la existencia de Abuelo Pitufo, esta segura de que lograra sorprender a la reina con su captura. Por supuesto, Hogata debe atrapar primero a Abuelo Pitufo...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Labrador esconde su amor por Pitufina ocultandose en el anonimato y enviandole poemas. Cuando finalmente se encuentran, Giganton les captura y, en sus esfuerzos por escapar, descubren su afecto mutuo.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Filosofo y Bebe Pitufo mezclan las formulas de Papa Pitufo con consecuencias desastrosas, dejandoles a merced de un ejercito de hambrientas langostas que Gargamel ha soltado en el bosque.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: La nota que Papa Pitufo escribio avisando a los demas Pitufos para que vean un cometa esta rota. Al ser solo capaces de leer una parte, los Pitufos creen que es el fin del mundo. Todos planean como sera su ultimo dia, hasta que papa Pitufo regresa y clarifica el lio.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cada vez que Pitufo Perezoso se queda dormido, tiene la misma pesadilla una y otra vez: se encuentra en poder de Morfeo, un malvado hechicero que quiere capturar a tantas almas dormidas como sea posible. Uno tras otro, todos los Pitufos van cayendo en las garras de Morfeo. ¿Todos? Quiza no, si Papa Pitufo puede evitarlo. Para ello, Papa Pitufo acude al Arenero en busca de ayuda...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cuando se produce una emergencia, todos los Pitufos de la aldea dejan lo que tienen entre manos y corren a oir las noticias. Pero que Pitufo Vanidoso convoque una asamblea para que los Pitufos puedan admirar su nuevo gorro es pasarse de la raya. Le echan de la aldea y Pitufo Vanidoso tiene la mala suerte de encontrarse con Lofty, el elfo, que le recomienda darse un horrible bano de fango...

programme.title: Los Pitufos Y El Arbol Del Dinero
programme.desc: El mago malvado Gargamel ha elaborado otro plan diabolico con la ayuda de su madre, quien no es mas agradable que el. El quiere persuadir a los Pitufos con dinero pero ellos no saben lo que les espera. ¿Pitufo Goloso caera en la trampa?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El malvado mago Gargamel quiere crear un monstruo. Una criatura horrible y gigantesca, ¡un ser imponente que destruya a todos los Pitufos! Pero Gargamel comete un pequeno error y el resultado les dejara asombrados a su gato Azrael y a el.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: La malvada bruja se transforma en Pitufo para vengarse de ellos por destruir su amuleto magico.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: La nueva obra de Pitufo Poeta va a ser su mayor creacion de todos los tiempos, y contara con Pitufina, la preferida de todos, como actriz principal. Los demas Pitufos compiten por el honor de actuar junto a Pitufina. Incluso Pitufo Timido, que es muy discreto y retraido, es uno de los candidatos al papel. Pero Pitufo Filosofo, que se ha autodesignado director de la obra, no lo ve de la misma manera...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: El Pitufo Que Queria Ser Rey
programme.desc: Pitufo Sonador anhela convertirse en rey despues de leer una historia sobre reyes. Mientras esta en su barco, cae a traves de un remolino y llega a una tierra de pequenos seres que creen que Pitufo Sonador es su rey, desaparecido hace mucho tiempo. Cuando se enfrenta a los Norfnangs, los enemigos de esos pequenos seres, descubre que no son terrorificos en absoluto. Pitufo Sonador se da un golpe en la cabeza y descubre al despertar que todo habia sido un sueno, aunque encuentra en su gorro una joya identica a las que extraian esos pequenos seres de su mina.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Labrador es el reticente amo de un genio llamado Gourdy, cuyo entusiasmo por ser servicial es quiza algo excesivo. Tras un nuevo incidente provocado por el exceso de celo de Gourdy, Pitufo Labrador le dice algo que no deberia haber dicho y Gourdy desaparece. ¿Y a que no adivinas quien lo encuentra? En efecto: Escrupuloso, el aprendiz del malvado mago Gargamel. ¿Y quien podria arrebatar a Gourdy de las manos de Escrupuloso, sino el propio Gargamel?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufitos se sienten poco queridos y deciden huir. Se llevan consigo objetos que les recuerden su hogar, lo que hace que los Pitufos crean que hay un ladron entre ellos. Pitufo Filosofo intenta atrapar al ladron instalando pitufialarmas. Las alarmas provocan un estruendo que atrae a los Pitufitos de vuelta a casa, donde Papa Pitufo les convence de que los quieren.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El malvado mago Gargamel crea una formula magica que duplica todo aquello que toca. Y...¡sorpresa! ¡Ahora hay seis Pitufos Filosofos! Esto provoca algunas situaciones interesantes en la aldea... ¡Y tambien en casa de Gargamel!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Fortachon descubre a un caballero que lo ayuda a combatir a un Dragon, pero este huye y deja a Fortachon defendiendo a los Pitufos.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Un terrible gigante ayuda a Gargamel a capturar a los Pitufos para hacer una rica sopa, pero tendra que enfrentar a Papa Pitufo primero.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Gargamel ha echado tantas sustancias toxicas en su estanque que el agua se vuelve encantada. Tras caerse en el estanque, Gargamel se vuelve pequeno, tan pequeno que Papa Pitufo tendra que salvarlo.

programme.title: El Capricho De Travieso
programme.desc: ¿Sabias que, si atrapas un trol, este puede concederte un deseo? Resulta que Aloysius el trol ha quedado atrapado en una de las pitufitrampas de Gargamel. Pitufo Colerico le libera y, como recompensa, consigue que los demas Pitufos satisfagan todos sus caprichos. Esto acarrea un monton de problemas para los Pitufos, ya que los Pitufitos, en ocasiones, piden cosas que no son buenas para ellos... ni tampoco para los demas.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Esta vez, Gargamel tiene un plan infalible. Sin hacer caso de la risa burlona de Azrael, el malvado hechicero ha perfeccionado una sustancia magica a la que ha llamado «polvo temerario», que convertira a todos los Pitufos en temerarios e intrepidos aventureros. ¿Caera Papa Pitufo en la trampa de Gargamel? ¿Atrapara su enemigo a todos los Pitufos? ¿Tendra esta historia un final feliz?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Gargamel esta decidido a sobrevolar la Aldea Pitufa para atrapar a un Pitufo y llevarlo a la Convencion de los Magos, e invoca a su libro de hechizos para que le ayude. Esto da lugar a una serie de divertidos contratiempos con su maquina voladora, y Gargamel vuelve a convertirse en el hazme reir de la Convencion de los Magos.

programme.title: La Carrera De Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Carpintero ha ideado un nuevo invento: el pitufimovil. Todos los Pitufos tienen su propio vehiculo personalizado y todos (o casi todos) disfrutan dando una vuelta en ellos. Sin embargo, el malvado mago Gargamel se aprovecha de la idea y empieza a causar problemas a los Pitufos...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos hambrientos descubren una cueva en donde se encuentra oculta comida congelada custodiada por un trol tambien congelado quien fue encarcelado debido a su avaricia por un diamante magico. Mientras los Pitufos descongelan la cueva Gargamel roba la comida, pero el diamante magico lo transforma en una masa helada y el trol liberado ayuda gustosamente a los Pitufos a cargar la comida de regreso a su aldea.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: La encantadora Allura posee una esfera magica muy especial cuya energia, segun ella misma dice, puede levantar el animo e inspirar a aquellos faltos de inspiracion. Todo lo que hay que hacer es sostener la esfera con las manos... Es cierto que la esfera fomenta la inspiracion, pero solo hasta cierto punto. Sin embargo, sus efectos secundarios pueden ser muy peligrosos, tal como descubren los Pitufos cuando se hacen adictos a la esfera...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Practico aprende que es mejor haber pitufado que no haber pitufado nunca cuando descubre que su amor verdadero es una sirena. ¿Podran vivir juntos para siempre?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El chico del bosque y Laconia, la elfa muda y sorda, preguntan a Papa Pitufo que celebre su boda. Mientras los Pitufos preparan la fiesta bajo las ordenes de Pitufina, Gargamel hace acto de presencia.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: La vida en la Aldea Pitufa podria ser mas tranquila si Puppy se comportara un poco mejor. Sin embargo, el pequeno perro de los Pitufos se dedica a escarbar entre las flores de Pitufina, ensuciar el nuevo papel pintado de Pitufo Vanidoso y arruinar los experimentos de Papa Pitufo. Aun asi, Puppy va a ayudar a los Pitufos a escapar de una trampa que les ha tendido Gargamel. O quiza no tenga la disciplina necesaria para ello...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: A Todas Las Criaturas Grandes Y Pequenas
programme.desc: Pitufo Natural esta convencido de que puede ayudar a todas las criaturas con sus dones curativos, incluso al malvado Azrael, cuya pata queda atrapada en una trampa. El gato se cura y, a pesar de que tiene la tentacion de quedarse con los Pitufos, regresa con Gargamel, pero conduce a su dueno hacia un lugar alejado de la Aldea Pitufa.

programme.title: El Hombre De La Luna
programme.desc: Cansado y harto de que no le aprecien, el Hombre de la Luna deja su trabajo y se retira en la Tierra, en la Aldea Pitufa. La ausencia de la luna en cuarto creciente desata el caos en las costumbres de los Pitufos, y Madre Naturaleza y Padre Tiempo tambien se ven arrastrados por el embrollo...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Fortachon descubre lo que es estar incapacitado cuando se rompe la pierna. Pitufo Carpintero crea para el una pitufisilla de ruedas, un invento que le proporcionara algo de movilidad a Pitufo Fortachon. Pero, de repente, el malvado mago Gargamel aparece en escena.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: La Primera Navidad De Bebe Pitufo
programme.desc: La ilusion de Navidad se ve frustrada cuando Chlorhydris hechiza a San Nicolas para que no pueda repartir felicidad en Navidad. Afortunadamente, Papa Pitufo y los demas pitufos consiguen romper el hechizo y devolver la Navidad a su bosque.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Simon se ha perdido en el bosque buscando a sus padres, una pareja de gigantes. Los Pitufos trataran de llevarlo de vuelta a su casa, pero gargamel aparecera una vez mas con no muy buenas intenciones.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: La nota que Papa Pitufo escribio avisando a los demas Pitufos para que vean un cometa esta rota. Al ser solo capaces de leer una parte, los Pitufos creen que es el fin del mundo. Todos planean como sera su ultimo dia, hasta que papa Pitufo regresa y clarifica el lio.

programme.title: BRUCE LE'S GREATEST REVENGE - La Gran Revancha de Bruce Lee
programme.desc: Bruce Lee interpreta a un estudiante en una escuela de artes marciales, cuyo maestro se niega a ayudar a los revolucionarios chinos en ciernes a aprender kung fu en preparación para resistir a los japoneses. Bruce, sin embargo, no es de los que se echan atrás ante un desafío, los gritos de cobardía de la corte o se sientan de brazos cruzados mientras las mujeres chinas son abusadas. Su tendencia es golpear a muchos de los hombres y luchadores japoneses que conoce, lo que al final enfurece mucho a los japoneses.

programme.title: MISSION INFERNO - Infierno de la Mision

programme.title: DUEL of the 7 TIGERS - La Furia de los 7 Tigres
programme.desc: Derrotado en un combate en Shaolin, Wu Kung vaga por China hasta que encuentra su propio templo y estilo de lucha: Tang Sao Do Karate. Años más tarde, estudiante y noveno sucesor, Hsi Man Kwong desafía y desmorona todas las escuelas chinas de kung fu de la zona.

programme.title: DRAGON ON SHAOLIN TOWER - Dragon en la Torre Shaolin
programme.desc: Tras su invasión de Taiwán en 1874, los japoneses se unieron con una lengua siniestra para celebrar un torneo de artes marciales en un plan para desarraigar y asesinar a los principales combatientes de la resistencia de la región, rompiendo así el espíritu del patriotismo chino. Dos maestros locales de maestros de kung-fu demuestran ser más que un rival para los invasores.

programme.title: Mientras el lobo no está
programme.desc: A teenager and his misfit friends escape from their strict boarding school.

programme.title: La Virgen de Guadalupe
programme.desc: Every December 12 the devotion to the Virgin of Guadalupe is renewed in Mexico. In this devotion and beliefs, the history itself, the idiosyncrasy, the strengths and weaknesses of a people are reflected. Stories of people who, from the most remote places of the country, come to the Basilica of Guadalupe to rediscover their own history.

programme.title: 180 Grados
programme.desc: Salvador Diaz is a skilled conman. For most of his years, he cheated others for a living... until he cheated the wrong man. After messing with Martin Soto, Salvador's life now lies in the hands (or rather, the knee) of Gasparotto, an injured sports star who's flawlessness in the playing field becomes the most important factor not only for 'bringing in the big bucks', but for claiming his life back. Getting the people to believe in Gasparotto is Salvador's greatest act of con artistry yet. It will be in this moment of his life where he finally meets his true destiny. That is, if he can still believe in something higher than just himself.

programme.title: El mariachi gringo
programme.desc: A stifled, small-town man stuck in a dead end life, runs away to Mexico to be a mariachi singer. MARIACHI GRINGO is a musical tour-de-force exploring the reality of "following your dreams" across cultural, personal, social and geographical borders.

programme.title: La última noticia
programme.desc: A Peruvian radio host risks his life to report on clashes between police and militant guerrillas.

programme.title: Bendita rebeldía
programme.desc: Beatriz, a failed psychologist, flees to her childhood home to escape fraud charges, only to discover that her quirky aunt has turned the estate into a high school. What seems at first a terrible surprise will in fact help her finally find a fulfilling path in life as an unconventional theatre instructor.

programme.title: Recuperando a mi ex
programme.desc: A retired couple will have to defend their home against an unpredicted menace: Their kids moving back.

programme.title: Implacable
programme.desc: Max is a teenager who imagines himself as an implacable ladies man who can get any girl he wants. His life will take a 180º turn when he takes Dan, a smart, athletic and handsome twenty-something, under his wing and teaches him everything he knows. None of them imagined that this would make them compete for the affection of the same girl.

programme.title: La Sra. Haidi
programme.desc: One stormy night, a house near a little-traveled road. Mrs. Haidi lives there, alone in the company of her dogs. An accident on the road, a couple: Pablo and Mara, who seek help, but cannot imagine the nightmare they will experience that night. A psychological thriller that surprises every painting.

programme.title: Fuga de la Patagonia
programme.desc: Escape from Patagonia is a gaucho-western film set in the tumultuous Patagonia of late nineteenth century. It's a story of survival, based on real facts from the personal diary of the Argentinian pioneer Francisco P. Moreno.

programme.title: Como te ves, me vi
programme.desc: The story presents a dysfunctional family, whose problems are accentuated by the difficult relationship between a father and his adolescent son. Narrated in two timelines, present and past, the director reflects on adulthood to recall that the father once was also young.

programme.title: Ella es Ramona
programme.desc: Ramona is a fat woman with too much weight and barely any luck, her universe seems to be collapsing after a series of unfortunate events. But everything will soon get better thanks to some magical beetles she finds in a Tarot café.

programme.title: El elegido
programme.desc: A man named Jacques Mornard arrives in Mexico in 1940, claiming to be a Belgian who is fleeing the war in Europe to join his girlfriend, one of refugee Leon Trotsky's secretaries. But nobody knows that in reality this conventional and cheerful young man is in fact an agent of the Soviet Secret Service and has been sent to assassinate Trotsky.

programme.title: Bellas de noche
programme.desc: Portraits of a group of famous showgirls who started out in Mexico's burlesque culture during the disco era.

programme.title: La creciente
programme.desc: Matia, a marginal young man, escapes to an island in the River Paraná. In an uncomfortable atmosphere that is not his own, he tries to start a new life, but the tensions his arrival cause take him back to his criminal past and to the idea of having to flee in order to survive.

programme.title: Los dos rivales
programme.desc: Los Treviño y Los Guereña mantienen una rivalidad originada muchos anos atrás. Pues a raíz de esto y por necesidad de dinero, el heredero de los Treviño (Antonio Aguilar) y la heredera de los Guereña (Lucha Villa) tienen que disfrazarse usando ropa del sexo opuesto hasta lograr su cometido que es el de proteger y vender sus ranchos. Pero sucede lo inesperado y cambia los rumbos de sus destinos.

programme.title: Los diablos del terror
programme.desc: A federal police officer arrives in a town devastated by a hooded sect that leaves the face of satan on its victims.

programme.title: Jesús, María y José
programme.desc: The persecution instigated by King Herod prompts Joseph and Mary to flee with baby Jesus through the desert of Egypt, where the child learns his first words. Joseph works as a carpenter, but when he is asked to build a cross to execute a thief, he refuses and goes back to Nazareth.

programme.title: La mujer sin alma
programme.desc: Teresa (Maria Felix) is a beautiful, young, middle-class woman who is determined to climb the social ladder.To that end she employs her beauty and her charms to manipulate rich men while playing with their emotions.

programme.title: La madrecita
programme.desc: A picturesque indigenous woman pretends to be a nun and experiences a series of entanglements with the convent authorities.

programme.title: Jóvenes y bellas
programme.desc: Furious that his daughter Raquel spends her life running go-karts, dancing and singing rock, Ricardo sends her camping with her friends. On a ranch next to the girls' camp, Rubén and his brothers Rafael, Roque and Raúl build a school commissioned by his father Gumaro Paz, who prohibits them from dealing with women.

programme.title: En peligro de muerte
programme.desc: Viruta and Capulina look for gold in the West, but are captured by Indians. With a metal detector and the flash of a camera they will have to win the respect of the Indians and save the attractive young women Lupita and Lolita.

programme.title: Lo que le pasó a Sansón
programme.desc: El vago Tin Tan y su celosa novia, la peinadora Lila, van al cine a ver "Sansón y Dalila". De regreso a casa Tin Tan sueña con que él es Sansón y Lila es Dalila. En el sueño, Sansón tiene amores con Miriam, pero cae hechizado por la belleza de Dalila, quien le roba la fuerza al cortarle el cabello. Sansón recupera su fuerza y se enfrenta al príncipe Arthur.

programme.title: Tonta, tonta, pero no tanto
programme.desc: India Maria decides to go live with a cousin in the Mexican capital to find a good job, but all kinds of complications arise.

programme.title: La flecha envenenada
programme.desc: A young orphan is attacked by Apaches and must pay her father's debts, since she may be dispossessed of her land.

programme.title: La edad de la tentación
programme.desc: Un grupo de jóvenes se rebela contra la sociedad. Con Gastón Santos.

programme.title: Santo contra Capulina
programme.desc: Capulina is a night-watchman in a warehouse, a perfect job for him. When some thieves break in and steal some crates, El Santo is after them because they are using the warehouse for diamond smuggling. Capulina hinders their capture. Then he decides that he will put on a wrestler's mask and help El Santo to capture the crooks.

programme.title: El grito de la muerte
programme.desc: A cowboy and his partner are involved in an action adventure wanting to obtain information about a stone figure of a woman crying.

programme.title: Si me han de matar mañana
programme.desc: La vida de un hombre cambia totalmente cuando encuentra a su hija, que había sido secuestrada años atrás por unos villanos.

programme.title: Rosario
programme.desc: Rosario y Carlos, esposos, forman parte parte de una compañía de teatro. En una escena de celos, ella debe disparar y matarlo. Carlos ha tenido una aventura con Zulma, otra actriz de la compañía, lo que no ha ocultado. La normalidad vuelve al matrimonio, y ese mismo día en la escena final del drama que representaban Rosario y Carlos, ella mata accidentalmente a su marido. Alguien cambio la pistola....

programme.title: Cómicos y Canciones
programme.desc: Viruta y Capulina son reporteros de un periódico e intentan obtener la notoriedad y entrevistan a un asesino que se da cuenta que no son músicos.

programme.title: El Espejo de la Bruja
programme.desc: Un esposo asesina a su esposa, y años más tarde su fantasma emerge del espejo de una bruja para vengarse.
